<div style="--primary-color: #008475;" class="faq-group {{ border_bottom ? 'has-border-bottom' : '' }}">
  <h3>{{ "Related questions" }}</h3>

  {% embed 'parc:faq' %}
    {% block question %}
      {{ "Can we live a \"chemical-free\" life? " | t }}
    {% endblock %}
    {% block answer %}
      {{ "No - everything around us, including air, water, food, and our own bodies, is made of chemicals, but we can reduce exposure to harmful or unnecessary synthetic chemicals." | t }}
    {% endblock %}
  {% endembed %}

  {% embed 'parc:faq' %}
    {% block question %}
      {{ "What are \"forever chemicals\"?" | t }}
    {% endblock %}
    {% block answer %}
      {{ "“Forever chemicals” are PFAS (per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances) - man-made chemicals that don’t break down easily in the environment or the human body and can build up over time, potentially causing health and environmental harm." | t }}
    {% endblock %}
  {% endembed %}


  {% embed 'parc:faq' %}
    {% block question %}
      {{ "How are chemicals regulated?" | t }}
    {% endblock %}
    {% block answer %}
      {{ "Chemicals are regulated through government laws and agencies that require testing, risk assessment, and limits on how chemicals are made, used, and released to protect human health and the environment." | t }}
    {% endblock %}
  {% endembed %}
</div>
